HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 484
By Haston
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Cooper Townley, 2025
Salutatorian of Hardin County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Townley is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
Salutatorian of the 2025 graduating class at Hardin County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Townley has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Cooper Townley has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including student council, National Honor Society, English Honor Society, Vocational Honor
Society, football, soccer, FCA, and Hopewell Baptist Church's student ministry; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Townley well exhibited his outstanding leadership skills and manifold
talents as the reporter and president of the school chapter of the National Honor Society, the
captain of the varsity football team, a Tennessee Secondary School Athletic Association
(TSSAA) Scholastic Merit Athlete for four years, a Courier Scholar Athlete, a delegate to Boys
State, a delegate to the Tennessee Electric Cooperative Association Youth Leadership Summit,
a member of Hardin County High School's Youth Leadership program, and as an FAA-certified
drone pilot; and
