WHEREAS, apart from his superlative scholastic endeavors, he has also generously
given of his time to serve on the Hopewell Baptist Church Youth Missions Team, where he has
assisted with various residential improvement and repair tasks and led youth camps; the
Hopewell Baptist Church Media Team, where he acts as a technology media specialist for
Sunday events; and VOLS, where he and other Hardin County High School students have aided
local community organizations and events with myriad projects; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Townley, with an indefatigable industriousness, has also helped to
foster the next generation of athletes as a TSSAA-registered football official for middle school
and junior varsity games and a Savannah Parks and Recreation youth football and baseball
official; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Townley's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for his future success; and
WHEREAS, Cooper Townley's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride
for his family, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Townley's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor the 2025 Hardin County High School
Salutatorian, Cooper Townley, on his impressive academic achievement and extend to him our
best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
